ns.; Improved and enhanced effectiveness of the safety training programme; Reviewed Manuals, Emergency Response Procedures and cultivated to improve; Directed Summer preparedness at project sites.; AFCONS INFRASTRUCTURE LTD. KOCHI, PIPAVAV, VERAVAL & MUMBAI; Safety Officer2 for Marine facilities project of Oct 2009 to July 2011 at Kochi; for LNG Terminal at Petronet LNG Ltd.; Safety Officer for Conversion of India largest Wet Dock to Jul 2007 to Sep2009 at Pipavav; Dry Dock and fabrication of 600 Ton capacity Goliath Crane; projects for Pipavav Shipyard Limited, Rajula, Gujarat; Safety Officer for Intake & Effluent C for channel pipe line, July 2006 to June 2007 at Veraval; Construction of pump house and Drilling & Blasting for Intake; & Effluent pipeline at Gujarat Heavy Chemical Ltd.; Safety Officer for Tata Power Coal Jetty with Slipway project Oct 2005 to July 2006 at Mumbai; Managed project sites at a time of around 1500 employees, simultaneously led HSE team of 8 direct reports.; Developed, implemented and tested emergency response plans.; Collaborated closely with Health Centre for developing Health Alerts, periodic medical check-up and for health; awareness programme.; Ensured routine maintenance of Fire extinguishers upkeep portable fire extinguishers.; Mentored HSE team for celebrating Road Safety Week, National Safety Day/Week, Fire Service Day, World; Environment Day to motivate employees towards safety.; KIRLOSKAR BROTHERS LIMITED BOISAR, MUMBAI; Safety Officer for Construction of Pump House, commissioning Mar 2005 to Sep.2005; of Auxiliary of Service Water & Condenser Cooling Water Pump; projects for Nuclear Power Corporation of India Limited; Increased understanding of hazard identification and incident management across the site.; Performed workplace inspections for machineries, tools and safety equipment to identify and; correct potential hazards.; Assisted gang leaders/supervisors for conducting Toolbox Meeting.; Organized HSE Trainings, Meetings W